COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x18a
STRING: [Phorni] “Hey... Are you going out somewhere?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1a0
STRING: [Chris] “Hm? Yeah, it's about dinner time, isn't it?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1d2
STRING: [Phorni] “Oh, you're eating out tonight?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1e8
STRING: [Chris] “Yeah, that's the plan.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1fe
STRING: Since making plans with Fal yesterday, I found myself
unable to relax.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x214
STRING: I lent a helping hand to the person I may end up
partnering up with, and she's treating me to dinner as
thanks.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x22a
STRING: That's all it was.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x236
STRING: But perhaps it was a matter of conscience, as Phorni
seemed to realize something was weighing on me.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x24c
STRING: I spent my day reading books, playing my Fortelle, fine
tuning songs that I never intended to actually perform.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x26c
STRING: It was just like any other Saturday that I spend waiting
for a letter from Arie to arrive.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x282
STRING: Torta would sometimes invite me over for a meal, but
that was a relatively rare occurrence.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x298
STRING: [Chris] “I'm kind of surprised you noticed.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x2ca
STRING: [Phorni] “We have spent a lot of time together, you
know.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x2e0
STRING: [Chris] “I guess you're right, two years is a long time.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x312
STRING: [Phorni] “That's right!

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x340
STRING: So? Dinner with Asino?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x34c
STRING: [Chris] “No, I'm going to Fal's...”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x37e
STRING: [Phorni] “What?! Dinner together?

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x3ac
STRING: What's this
‘going to Fal's’ business...?

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x3da
STRING: I'm telling Arie!”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x3e6
STRING: [Chris] “Look, just be quiet and listen, would you?
There's two things I want to say...”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x404
STRING: [Phorni] “...What do you have to say then?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x41a
STRING: [Chris] “First, I haven't finished explaining, so if you're
going to harass me about it, at least wait until I'm
finished.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x456
STRING: [Phorni] “And?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x46c
STRING: [Chris] “You can't actually tell Arie, you know...”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x49e
STRING: [Phorni] “Phooey! It's not that hard to write an itsy-bitsy
little addition to your letters.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x4be
STRING: [Chris] “See, now this is the problem with weird little
fairies. I'll ask just for the sake of it, but can you really
tell her?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x4fa
STRING: [Phorni] “You bet I can.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x510
STRING: [Chris] “How?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x526
STRING: With an unexplainably confident grin on her face, Phorni
flew over to the desk and used her entire body to lift up
the pen that was sitting there.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x562
STRING: [Chris] “Oho, What are you going to do now?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x580
STRING: [Phorni] “Write!”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x596
STRING: There happened to be a piece of paper on the desk,
just waiting to be written on.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x5a2
STRING: Probably the one I planned to use to write my letter
tomorrow.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x5ae
STRING: [Chris] “What are you going to write, hmm?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x5cc
STRING: [Phorni] “Something you don't want Arie to know about!”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x5e2
STRING: [Chris] “This should be good...”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x5f8
STRING: At this point I didn't really care.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x604
STRING: It was still half past six.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x610
STRING: The trattoria wasn't that far away, so I was sure I'd have
enough time to watch this spectacle then head over
there.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x62e
STRING: [Phorni] “Hrnngh! ...Oomph, hah!”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x66e
STRING: After all that effort, the word she needed a whole
minute to write was...

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x698
STRING: “Momma's boy”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x6e6
STRING: [Phorni] “Done!”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x6fc
STRING: [Chris] “Phorni...?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x71a
STRING: [Phorni] “What?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x730
STRING: [Chris] “There's three things I want to say.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x77a
STRING: [Phorni] “T-That's more than before.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x790
STRING: [Chris] “First, your writing is terrible.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x7c2
STRING: [Phorni] “There's not much I can do about that...”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x7d8
STRING: [Chris] “Second, do you know how long that took? Even
if you did it in the middle of the night, I'd notice with all
those grunts you let out.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x814
STRING: [Phorni] “Th-That's because I...”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x82a
STRING: [Chris] “Third, the envelope would already be sealed.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x85c
STRING: [Phorni] “Gah...”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x872
STRING: [Chris] “Fourth.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x8a4
STRING: [Phorni] “Th-There's four now?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x8ba
STRING: [Chris] “I get that you wanted to tease me. But what's
the point of writing a letter to Arie?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x8f6
STRING: [Phorni] “Well, I... Uh...”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x90c
STRING: [Chris] “Okay, I see. Well, thank you for the
entertainment.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x93e
STRING: [Phorni] “Ugh...”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x954
STRING: [Chris] “You've made it very clear you can't actually tell
her, not that you need to anyway.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x990
STRING: [Phorni] “Excuse me...? You're the one saying you're
going out to dinner with some girl! And what do you
mean by ‘going to Fal's?’!”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x9ba
STRING: [Chris] “The first thing I said. Wait till I'm finished... Or
have you already forgotten?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x9d8
STRING: [Phorni] “Of course I haven't.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x9ee
STRING: [Chris] “Fal's part-time job is at a trattoria called
’Copert.’ It's not so far from here.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xa2a
STRING: [Phorni] “That's what you meant by ‘Fal's?’”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xa40
STRING: If only she had just listened that little bit more, it all
would have made sense...

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xa56
STRING: But Phorni kind of had a habit of jumping to
conclusions, or just not thinking things through.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xa6c
STRING: [Chris] “That's right.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xa9e
STRING: [Phorni] “Oh... I see.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xab4
STRING: Phorni seemed a bit down for one reason or another, so
begrudgingly I tried to cheer her up.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xaca
STRING: [Chris] “Well... There is a reason as to why she's
treating me to dinner. I helped her with something at
school yesterday. So your shaky suspicions aren't
completely... Shaky.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xafc
STRING: [Phorni] “R-Right?

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xb2a
STRING: This is all your fault, isn't it, Chris?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xb36
STRING: [Chris] “I'm being incredibly nice right now you know?
Let's say it's nobody's fault.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xb5e
STRING: [Phorni] “O-Oh, right.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xb8c
STRING: Okay.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xb98
STRING: Phorni seemed to be seeing things my way.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xba4
STRING: Trying hard not to roll my eyes, I looked at my watch. It
was almost time for me to head out.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xbba
STRING: [Chris] “...Okay, I'll see you later then.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xbec
STRING: [Phorni] “Sure. Enjoy your meal!”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xc2e
STRING: I jogged through the streets in the rain, and soon
reached my destination.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xc84
STRING: [Clerk] “Good evening, welcome!”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xc9a
STRING: I was casually guided to a table, and for just a brief
moment I pondered what I should order.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xcb0
STRING: Should I just choose whatever I felt like eating?

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xcc6
STRING: While I was looking at the menu trying to make up my
mind, I heard a familiar voice from inside the kitchen.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xce4
STRING: [Fal] “Oh, that's him!”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xcfa
STRING: The server who had come to take my order had
apparently also heard the same voice.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xd18
STRING: [Clerk] “We have already received your order, sir. Your
meal will be ready shortly.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xd2e
STRING: The server was most polite, and left me with a smile
before returning to the kitchen.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xd44
STRING: Anyway, it seemed that Fal knew I was here, and she
had already decided my order for me.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xd5a
STRING: There wasn't much point in thinking about anything else
now.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xd66
STRING: Relaxing into my seat, I looked around the trattoria.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xd72
STRING: As one would expect from a place that serves
home-style cooking, the atmosphere was quite relaxing.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xd88
STRING: The interior was beautiful, and stylish in a way that was
probably popular with young people.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xd9e
STRING: As I'd expected, there was a table with a few faces I
recognized from school.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xdb4
STRING: After having a look about, I drank some of my water
and made myself at home.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xe04
STRING: [Clerk] “Thank you for waiting.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xe1a
STRING: A short time later, the waiter brought me a plate of
food.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xe30
STRING: Upon the silver plate was a neatly placed serving of
lasagne, which steamed deliciously.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xe6a
STRING: [Fal] “Good evening. You're right on time!”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xe80
STRING: [Chris] “I thought I was going to be slightly late, but I
guess I made it.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xe9e
STRING: [Fal] “Well, your timing was surprisingly good.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xeb4
STRING: [Chris] “So, did everything work out okay?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xed2
STRING: [Fal] “It did. I asked the boss to let me take my break
now, so it's okay.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xef2
STRING: She had her white, sanitary looking apron tucked under
one arm. She must have removed it just before coming
over.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xf08
STRING: Fal sat down in the seat across from me.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xf14
STRING: [Chris] “Isn't this a busy time, though? It seems pretty
packed in here.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xf34
STRING: It seemed that I had been fortunate, as a lot of other
customers poured in after me.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xf4a
STRING: There were a few people seated outside the restaurant
under the cover of the roof, waiting to get a table.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xf68
STRING: [Fal] “It's fine, I've already done my share of the work.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xf96
STRING: More importantly,

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xfc4
STRING: if you let it get cold, it won't taste
as good.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xfd0
STRING: Passing me a knife and fork, Fal sat there staring at me
with a smile on her face.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xfe6
STRING: [Chris] “You aren't just going to watch, are you...?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1018
STRING: [Fal] “Hm? Don't mind me, go ahead and eat.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x102e
STRING: [Chris] “That's kinda hard to do when you're...”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x104c
STRING: [Fal] “How about I sit next to you, then?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1074
STRING: She moved over next to me the moment she finished
her sentence.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1080
STRING: [Chris] “You're going to watch no matter what, huh?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x10b2
STRING: [Fal] “Well, if I don't do anything at all, they'll probably
kick us out of this table for four.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x10d2
STRING: [Chris] “I don't really mind that...”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1104
STRING: [Fal] “You don't want my break to go to waste, do you?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1124
STRING: [Chris] “Ah... Good point.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1156
STRING: [Fal] “Well, we're fine anyway.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1184
STRING: Now, eat up before it
really does get cold.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1190
STRING: Doing my best not to be bothered by Fal's gaze, I ate a
mouthful of the lasagne I had cut up.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x11a6
STRING: [Chris] “This is... Really good!”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x11d8
STRING: [Fal] “Isn't it? I made most of it myself, you know. I've
been working here for two years now, so it better be
good!”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x11f8
STRING: [Chris] “Did you used to cook before you started
working here?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x120e
STRING: We continued talking while I cautiously let my lasagne
cool down enough for me not to get burned by the
cheese.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1240
STRING: [Fal] “Why of course, yes. That's why I'm pretty good at
it now.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1256
STRING: [Chris] “I see... It does taste really good. I remember
eating lasagne somewhere a while ago, but it tasted
like rubber.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1292
STRING: [Fal] “I'm not sure that counts as food.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x12c0
STRING: This place isn't
that big, and the prices are pretty reasonable, but
the owner has a strict policy when it comes to
making good food.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x12e0
STRING: [Chris] “You look happy just talking about this, you
know. You really like cooking, huh?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1312
STRING: [Fal] “I do.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1328
STRING: [Chris] “There's nothing you can't do, huh... It almost
makes me lose confidence.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1364
STRING: [Fal] “Lose confidence?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x137a
STRING: [Chris] “Well, not exactly, but it just made me think that
I can't really do anything that compares to you.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x13b6
STRING: [Fal] “Oh, that's not true. I'm just doing the things that I
like, that's all. Helping people, cooking... And of course
my singing.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x13d6
STRING: Seeing her say this so joyfully reminded me how she
was when she sang.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x13e2
STRING: It wasn't so much that she was being modest, but more
that she seemed to be just expressing her honest
feelings.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1454
STRING: [Chris] “That was great.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1472
STRING: [Fal] “Did you like it?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1488
STRING: [Chris] “I really did, yeah. I might have to come back
again sometime.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x14ba
STRING: [Fal] “Just as a regular customer?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x14d0
STRING: [Chris] “Of course, but are you really sure I don't need
to pay for today...?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1502
STRING: [Fal] “I'm sure! I told you, this is my way of thanking you.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1530
STRING: But if you decide to come here regularly, I'm sure we
can give you some things on the house.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1550
STRING: [Chris] “Ha-ha, if that's the case then I'd be a fool not to
come back.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1582
STRING: [Fal] “I'm not actually trying to advertise but, come back
again sometime, okay?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1598
STRING: [Chris] “When I have the chance, sure!”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x15b6
STRING: [Fal] “Great.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x15e4
STRING: Hmm... I should probably get back to it.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x15f0
STRING: [Chris] “How long is your break?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1622
STRING: [Fal] “Only thirty minutes.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1650
STRING: I suppose I have to work
another... Hmm, two and a half hours?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x165c
STRING: [Chris] “Is it going to be hard?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x168e
STRING: [Fal] “It's not that, I was just thinking it's a shame.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x16a4
STRING: [Chris] “A shame...?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x16d6
STRING: [Fal] “That my break is over so soon.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1702
STRING: Saying that, she stood up and took the apron that she
had left sitting on the seat.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1734
STRING: [Fal] “I already let the staff at the cash register know, so
you can just head out when you're ready.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1754
STRING: [Chris] “Oh, okay, sure. Thanks again for the meal.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1772
STRING: [Fal] “See you again soon.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x178c
STRING: Perhaps she was in more of a rush than I had thought,
she was already putting on her apron as she
disappeared into the kitchen.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x17a2
STRING: I really did enjoy the food I had tonight, so I figured that
I would be back again some time.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x17b8
STRING: I didn't have any problems with cooking for myself at
home, but I have to admit it was nice to eat out for a
change.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x17ce
STRING: [Chris] “Thanks for the lovely meal.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x17ec
STRING: [Clerk] “Thank you very much!”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1802
STRING: I showed my appreciation to the staff at the cash
register and left the trattoria.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1888
STRING: [Phorni] “Oh, welcome home! How was dinner?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x189e
STRING: Phorni was still floating in the same place as she was
when I left, singing happily.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x18b4
STRING: Upon realizing that I had returned, she immediately
stopped and turned to face me.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x18ca
STRING: [Chris] “I'm home.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x18fc
STRING: [Phorni] “So, how was it?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1912
STRING: [Chris] “Hm? The food was great.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1944
STRING: [Phorni] “Oh, how nice.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x195a
STRING: [Chris] “What are you getting at?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x198c
STRING: [Phorni] “You were eating delicious food with a girl...”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x19a2
STRING: [Chris] “Didn't we already discuss this?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x19d4
STRING: [Phorni] “Well I started thinking about it again, but if she
was working, then doesn't that mean she cooked dinner
for you?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x19fe
STRING: [Chris] “Not necessarily... But that was the case tonight.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1a3a
STRING: [Phorni] “Ugh... If you want a girl to cook for you, you
could just go over to Torta's.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1a5a
STRING: [Chris] “I'm sure she has plenty of things to do instead.
And besides... Torta's cooking isn't exactly uh... You
know.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1a7a
STRING: Torta was like a childhood friend, and Phorni seemed
rather fond of her as she often brought her up like that.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1ab6
STRING: [Phorni] “Oh, I could cook for you then.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1acc
STRING: [Chris] “Let me just confirm... Cook what exactly?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1afe
STRING: [Phorni] “Meals, of course! Why would you ask such a

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1b14
STRING: [Chris] “How exactly? Can you even cook?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1b46
STRING: [Phorni] “Of course I can!”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1b5c
STRING: This was the second time I had seen that unexplainably
confident grin today.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1b68
STRING: [Chris] “I seriously doubt that.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1b9a
STRING: [Phorni] “Y-You don't think I can!”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1bb0
STRING: [Chris] “There's one thing I want to say.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1be2
STRING: [Phorni] “Gah... That's less than before.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1bf8
STRING: [Chris] “You're a bonehead...”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1c4a
STRING: And that's how my usual boring weekend passed.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1c56
STRING: Fal... Arie...

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1c62
STRING: I had a lot of things that I probably had to think about,
but instead I just focused on the letter that I would
receive from Arie tomorrow.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1c82
STRING: I had agreed to meet Ninna before that, but I was
wondering if I'd be able to make it on time.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1c98
STRING: My body was feeling heavy due to my belly being full of
lasagne, and a comfortable wave of drowsiness
gradually came over me.
